1LT Overton;

I want to, again, personally thank you for your technical proficiency in
generating plans for the above noted subject up to this point.

I just noted a discrepancy between the end time for Ph I and the start time
for Ph II. that time, I have just adjusted to 120520RMAY26.

What I'd like to do next is:

- create an execution timeline of OPORD taskings, starting 15 APR26 and
ending on 172359RMAY26. This timeline will highlight known exercise
execution action up to this point. For example, 152100RAPR26 S1 Provides
roster of personnel participating in the exercise; 120520RMAY26 Ph I
(Planning and Coordination) ends; and, 142131RMAY26 Ph II (Training
Execution) ends.

- Refine our personnel participation assessment, so that I can
beginning putting together sUAS and SECFOR Teams to execute tasking 14 MAY
26. This will enable me to make sure to request reinforcement from adjacent
RGTs if needed.

- Construct and initial coordinating draft of an operational brief to the
CG for 18 APR 26. I need to get this to the G3 beforehand as a pre-read /
read-ahead.


Here is my again revised copy of the OPORD that I mentioned above.

-- 
V/R

JOHN T. SHEAF
LTC, TNSG
S3, 3 RGT
717.673.6177
john.sheaf@tnstateguard.org

